node.text: When it's too hot out to turn on your oven, the time is right to experience the phenomenal crisp texture and flavor of grilled pizza. Happy Pride Month! Watch how the King Arthur Baking community is kicking off celebrations. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜

"We celebrate Pride because we are committed to a more diverse and inclusive future — and we want to show up for each other." - Karen Colberg, King Arthur Baking co-CEO

King Arthur Baking Company is making a donation to @TheTrevorProject, which provides crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer & questioning (LGBTQ) young people under 25. We encourage you to learn more and donate at bakewith.us/TrevorProject

node.title: Celebrate Pride With Us - King Arthur Baking Company - Pride 2021

node.text: With apple season kicked into full gear, we can’t NOT tell you about the #1 apple recipe on our website. Seriously, it’s ridiculous how good this is. Big chunks of juicy apples in a moist spice cake could be satisfying enough, but it’s the brown sugar frosting reminiscent of penuche fudge that puts this recipe over the top. Find this 5-star winner at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your batch of Old-Fashioned Apple Cake with Brown Sugar Frosting with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: Pancake tacos filled with fresh berries and whipped cream, with a bag of buttermilk pancake mix in the background. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text:
You’ve heard of breakfast tacos, but what about pancake tacos? Andy of @beautifuleatsandthings embraced fall flavors to create this clever twist on a breakfast classic. She shared:

“Fall is almost here and I’m celebrating with these Pumpkin Spice Pancake Tacos!

“Pancake tacos are such a fun way to add a little excitement to your breakfast meal! They are so easy to make, and you can stuff them with your favorite fruit! For this recipe, I used King Arthur’s Buttermilk Pancake Mix and added 2 teaspoons of pumpkin spice to the batter. I love using King Arthur’s pancake mixes because it cuts my prep time in half. Most of their pancake mixes only require the addition of water which saves me a lot of time in the kitchen, especially during those busy mornings! There are several varieties to choose from: Buttermilk, Confetti, Gluten-Free Classic, Gluten-Free Protein, and Carb-Conscious.

“After I cooked my Pumpkin Spice Pancakes, I placed them in these nifty little taco holders and stuffed them with blueberries and strawberries! And for the finishing touch, I added a dollop of whipped cream! Sooo good!”

Which mix will you make tacos from? Grab a bag at the link in our profile profile >> @kingarthurbaking and get creative! Share them with #KingArthurBaking.

node.text: Ah, apple pie. So perfect in its simplicity. Tender, flaky crust, warm spices, and in this case, about 43,000 slices of tangy-sweet apples. (Seriously, talk about a mile-high apple pie!) Find the recipe for our ultimate Apple Pie at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share yours with #KingArthurBaking

node.text: A grab-and-go twist on pancakes, these bite-sized Protein Pancake Bites are baked in a mini muffin pan and can be flavored with whichever mix-ins your heart desires! Easily prepped with just-add-water pancake mix (we used our protein one for an extra boost to start the day), flavor combos are endless. If you prefer sweet pancakes, maple-berry or banana-chocolate chip may catch your eye. Savory fans will love our bacon-cheddar rendition. How will you flavor your pancake bites? Let us know! Find the recipe and mix to get started at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your pancake bites with #KingArthurBaking

node.text: Hi! We’re the bakers of King Arthur, and sometimes, our bakes coming out of the oven look truly awful. If left out for the birds, those birds would turn their beaks up and fly over to see if the neighbor had tossed out anything better. But through failure came a valuable lesson: test bake, test bake, for the love of all that is good and buttery, TEST BAKE! Check out PJ’s latest blog at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking for her best tips on test baking cookies for sweet success. If you’ve had a baking blunder, share it with #KingArthurBaking so we won’t feel as bad about the birds ditching us for that blondie next door.

node.text: Tender, golden, and comfort incarnate straight from the oven, Baking Powder Biscuits are quick to prepare and even quicker to disappear from the dinner table. Find this crowd-pleasing recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your biscuits with #KingArthurBaking.

node.text: When a recipe has “rustic” in its title, you’re pretty much guaranteed to come off looking like a champ, even if things get a little wonky along the way. When a rustic treat also happens to highlight seasonal fruit, have an irresistibly flaky crust, and just be downright scrumptious, it's our kind of recipe! If you bake one thing this weekend, make it Rustic Fruit Tarts — they won’t let you down. Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your tarts with #KingArthurBaking.

node.text: Pooja Makhijani @laborofloaf is heating up the oil and getting ready to make a big batch of one of her favorite South Asian treats: Jalebi! Made with a slightly fermented batter and sugary syrup infused with fragrant saffron, this fried treat (reminiscent of funnel cake), is a crisp, spiraled delight for the senses. See how she creates these swirling sweets by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your batch of jalebi with #KingArthurBaking.

node.text: Celebrate #NationalOnlineLearningDay by conquering that baking goal you’ve been dreaming of through our Online Baking School! Perfect French Macarons, sourdough bread, bagels — what will you master? Find the perfect class for you on our fall calendar at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your creations with #KingArthurBaking.

node.text: Ah, the beginning of the week. We meet again. If Monday isn’t courteously greeting you with a hug and hot beverage, win the week by kicking it off with a sweet treat. With a mug, a microwave, and just over 5 minutes, vanilla cake is at your fingertips. (Monday will NEVER see it coming.) Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your mug cake with #KingArthurBaking
